Ingredients:
	Brisket 2-5 lbs	

	Vegetables: 
		Carrots
		Onions
		Potatoes
		Sweet potatoes 	/* optional */
		Parsnips 		/* optional */	

	Salt 
	Pepper
	Wine
	Apple juice

1. Pan sear all sides of the brisket in its own fat, until the outside is darkish brown. 
2. Put the brisket in a large baking pan, season with salt and pepper on both sides.
3. Put chopped vegetables into the baking pan, and add more salt and pepper. 
4. Add a little bit of wine and apple juice, enough to cover the bottom of the pan but not too much. 
5. Cook in the oven at 325F for 5 hours. 